{{Orphan|date=February 2013}}

In [[domain name system]]s, a '''lame delegation''', also known as a '''lame response''', is a type of [[error]] that results when a [[name server]] is designated as the authoritative server for a [[domain name]] for which it does not have authoritative data. 

The [[American Registry for Internet Numbers]] (ARIN) has a Draft Policies and Proposals concerning lame delegations  - Policy 2002-1: Lame Delegations in IN-ADDR.ARPA . See https://www.arin.net/policy/proposals/2002_1.html

