abac]] |'''Шaбац''' (Serbian, Macedonian), '''Šabac''' (English, Croatian, Bosnian, Slovene), '''Schabatz '''(German), '''Szabács '''(Hungarian), '''Böğürdelen''' (Turkish) |- |[[Štip]] |'''Štip''' (English, Croatian, Bosnian, Slovene), '''Штип''' (Serbian, Macedonian) |- | [[Stockholm]] | '''Estocolm''' (Catalan), '''Estocolmo''' (Galician, Portuguese, Spanish), '''Estokolmo''' (Tagalog[[:tl:Estokolmo|*]]), '''Holmia''' (Latin), '''Istūkhūlm''' (Arabic), '''Seutokholleum''' / '''Sŭt'okhollŭm''' – {{lang|ko|스톡홀름}} (Korean), '''Sīdégē'ěrmó''' – {{lang|zh|斯德哥爾摩}} (Chinese)[[:zh:斯德哥爾摩|*]], '''Stoccolma''' (Italian), '''Stockholbma''' (Sami), '''Stockholm''' (Basque, Danish, Dutch, Estonian, German, Hungarian, Norwegian, Romanian, Slovene, Swedish), '''Stócólm''' (Irish), '''Stoc Tholm''' (Scottish Gaelic, archaic), '''Stokgol'm''' - {{lang|ru|Стокгольм}} (Russian), '''Štokholm''' (Slovak), '''Stokholm''' (Albanian, Azeri, former Estonian, Serbian, Turkish), '''Stokholm''' – {{lang|bg|Стокхолм}} (Bulgarian), '''Stokhol'm''' (Ukrainian), '''Stokholma''' (Latvian), '''Stokholmas''' (Lithuanian), '''Stokholmo''' (Esperanto), '''Stokkhólmi''' – {{lang|el|Στοκχόλμη}} (Greek), '''Stokkhólmur''' (Faroese, Icelandic), '''Stokkolma''' (Maltese), '''Sutokkuhorumu''' - {{lang|ja|ストックホルム}} (Japanese)[[:ja:ストックホルム|*]], '''Sztokholm''' (Polish), '''Tukholma''' (Finnish),'''Sa-tok-home''' – {{lang|th|สตอกโฮล์ม}} (Thai)[[:th:สตอกโฮล์ม|*]] |- | [[Stargard Szczeciński]] | '''Stargard Szczeciński''' (Polish), '''Stargard in Pommern''' or '''Stargard an der Ihna''' (German), '''Stargardia''' (Latin), '''Stôrgard''' (Kashubian/Pomeranian), '''Stargarda Ščeciņska''' (Latvian), '''Ščecino Stargardas''' (Lithuanian), '''Στάργκαρντ Σετσέτσινσκι''' (Greek), '''Stargard Ščecin′ski''' - {{lang|ru|Старгард Щециньски}} (Russian), '''Stargard Ščecin′skyj''' - {{lang|uk|Старгард Щецінський}} (Ukrainian) |- | [[Stralsund]] | '''Stralsund''' (German, Swedish), '''Stralsunda''' (Italian), '''Strzałowo'''